					<tr valign="top">
						<td width="15">1)</td>
						<td>Cut skate in half and remove inner organs, tail, and hard part of the mouth.</td>
					</tr>
					<tr valign="top">
						<td width="15" class="o" align="right" style="padding-right:3px">*</td>
						<td class="o"> 
							When steaming whole skate, incise in the middle and remove inner organs and cut off tail and mouth.
						</td>
					</tr>	
					<tr><td colspan="2"><img src="/common/images/trans.gif" width="1" height="7" border="0"></td></tr>
					<tr valign="top">
						<td>2)</td>
						<td>Dry 2~3 days in a breezy shades.</td>
					</tr>
					<tr><td colspan="2"><img src="/common/images/trans.gif" width="1" height="7" border="0"></td></tr>
					<tr valign="top">
						<td>3)</td>
						<td>Mix seasoning and dip dried skate for 10 minutes and drain.</td>
					</tr>
					<tr><td colspan="2"><img src="/common/images/trans.gif" width="1" height="7" border="0"></td></tr>
					<tr valign="top">
						<td>4)</td>
						<td>Put skate in a steamer and steam once and then sprinkle seasoning on it. If a skate is big, sprinkle 3 times and if small, 2 times is enough. This makes skate evenly seasoned.</td>
					</tr>
					<tr><td colspan="2"><img src="/common/images/trans.gif" width="1" height="7" border="0"></td></tr>
					<tr valign="top">
						<td>5)</td>
						<td>Garnish skate with shredded green pepper, red pepper, seogi mushroom, and pan-fried yellow and white egg strips.</td>
